File::Shortcut is a Pure Perl Module to parse and manipulate Windows
Shortcut Files aka Shell Links (*.lnk).  It can be used to create
these files on systems which do not support the IShellLink interface
(ie. anything but Windows).

On Windows you might want to use Win32::Shortcut.


REQUIREMENTS

This module requires Perl 5.10 or later and the following additional
modules (from CPAN):

    * Try::Tiny


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc File::Shortcut
